{"default_url":null,"content":{"state":0,"taskInstructions":null,"references":[],"isTaskInstructionsVisible":true,"isCommentMandatory":false,"fields":[],"masterFinding":{"id":688753,"exploitInstructions":null,"verificationInstructions":"<b>Verification Instructions</b>\n\nIdentify parameters that could be used in LDAP queries. Login or search forms are the most typical uses for LDAP queries from web applications.\n\nAttempt to cause errors or unexpected results by injecting LDAP special characters: ), (, |, &#42;, !, &amp;.\n\nIf LDAP injection detected, attempt to expand the query result set. Typical injections:\n<ul><li>)(ou=&#42;</li>\n</ul>\nuser=&#42;)(uid=&#42;))(|(uid=&#42;\n\n%00 can sometimes be used to comment out the rest of the query (OpenLDAP).\n\n<b>Reporting Requirements</b>\n<ol><li>Screenshot the initial page</li>\n<li>Show the normal HTTP request</li>\n<li>Show LDAP injection in request parameter</li>\n<li>Show the impact of LDAP injection - typically authentication bypass or information enumeration</li>\n</ol>\n\n<b>Tools</b>\n\nIf LDAP injection detected, LDAPBlindExplorer can be used to extract data:\n<ul><li>http://code.google.com/p/ldap-blind-explorer/</li>\n</ul>\n","remediationInstructions":"The following recommendations will help reduce the risk of LDAP injection attacks:\n<ul><li>Ensure that the web application validates all input parameters (cookies, headers, query strings, forms, hidden fields, etc.) against a stringent definition of expected results. Allowlisting should be used as the base validation method of user input; blocklisting can be used as an additional layer of protection.</li>\n<li>Whenever possible, limit all client-supplied data to alphanumeric data. If non-alphanumeric characters must be used, encode them as before passing them to the underlying query.</li>\n</ul>\n","name":"LDAP Injection","sourceId":"M:688753","severity":"Medium","businessImpact":"A malicious user may be able to modify LDAP search queries which could lead to disclosure of sensitive data, thus compromising the confidentiality of the target system and its associated resources.","description":"LDAP injection was found within the application. LDAP injection is an attack that takes advantage of unsanitized user inputs that are used as part of LDAP queries. A malicious user may use LDAP injection to modify the dynamically generated LDAP query.\n"}}}